            <h1>Easy Pressure Cooker Pot Roast</h1>
            <img src="/images/easypressurecookerpotroast.jpg">
            <h2>A tender roast to enjoy on a cold day</h2>
            <p>This pot roast is a simple recipe that relies on keeping cool under pressure. Very flavorable and tender, it could be used for other means than just a roast. </p>
            <h3>Ingredients</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>2 tsp of Vegetable Oil</li>
                     <li>3 lbs of Boneless Beef Chuck Roast</li>
                      <li>1 pinch of Seasoned Salt</li>
                       <li>1 pinch of Onion Powder</li>
                        <li>1 pinch of Black Pepper</li>
                         <li> 1 14.5 ounce can of Beef Broth</li>
                          <li> 1 1/2 tsp of Worchester Sauce</li>
                            <li>1 large and sectioned Onion</li>
                              <li> 4 peeled and bite sized cut Carrots</li>
                                <li>4 large, peeled, and bite-sized Potatoes</li>
                          
                </ul>
                <h3>Steps</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Heat the oil in the pressure cooker while searing the roast on all sides in a hot skillet over medium heat.</li>
                     <li>Transfer and season the roast with black pepper, onion powder and seasoned salt.</li>
                     <li>Pour in beef broth and Worchester sauce, adding the onion and seal the lid.</li>
                      <li>Reduce heat to low and cook at full pressure for 30 minutes.</li>
                       <li>Lower pressure using quick release method to add carrots and potatoes, then reseal the lid.</li>
                        <li>Return the cooker to full pressure and cook for 15 more minutes.</li>
                </ol>
